1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,780
Hello everyone, welcome back to another great lesson with us here at EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎回到EnglishPod的另一堂精彩课程。

2
00:00:05,780 --> 00:00:06,780
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,780 --> 00:00:08,340
And I'm Erika.
我是Erika。

4
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:10,700
And today we're going out to eat.
今天我们要出去吃饭。

5
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,860
Yes, good thing too because I'm hungry.
是啊，正好我也饿了。

6
00:00:12,860 --> 00:00:14,580
I know, it's almost lunchtime.
我知道，快到午饭时间了。

7
00:00:14,580 --> 00:00:15,580
Yeah.
嗯。

8
00:00:15,580 --> 00:00:19,900
So today we're going to be talking about eating at a restaurant and giving some great recommendations
所以今天我们要讨论在餐厅吃饭，并给出一些很好的推荐

9
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:20,900
and suggestions.
和建议。

10
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:27,500
Yes, we have language for describing food, for describing restaurants and for making
是的，我们有描述食物、描述餐厅以及提出建议的语言。

11
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,500
suggestions.
建议。

12
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:32,460
Great, so let's start with our vocabulary preview for this lesson.
太好了，那么让我们从这节课的词汇预览开始。

13
00:00:32,460 --> 00:00:34,020
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

14
00:00:34,020 --> 00:00:39,460
We have two words today from our dialogue which you'll need to know to understand the
今天对话中有两个词你需要知道才能理解

15
00:00:39,460 --> 00:00:40,460
dialogue.
对话。

16
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:41,460
Great.
好的。

17
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:45,060
The first one that we have today is food poisoning.
今天第一个词是食物中毒。

18
00:00:45,060 --> 00:00:46,380
Food poisoning.
食物中毒。

19
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:47,460
Food poisoning.
食物中毒。

20
00:00:47,460 --> 00:00:48,780
Food poisoning.
食物中毒。

21
00:00:48,780 --> 00:00:51,140
So food poisoning is...
所以食物中毒是……

22
00:00:51,140 --> 00:00:52,140
Not a good thing.
不是好事。

23
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:53,820
Not a good thing.
不是好事。

24
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:58,740
It is when you eat some bad food and that food makes you sick.
就是当你吃了变质的食物，那食物让你生病。

25
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:00,860
So you get food poisoning.
所以你食物中毒了。

26
00:01:00,860 --> 00:01:03,980
Okay, so food poisoning, yeah, not a good thing.
好的，食物中毒，嗯，不是好事。

27
00:01:03,980 --> 00:01:05,820
Okay, the next word.
好的，下一个词。

28
00:01:05,820 --> 00:01:06,820
Allergic.
过敏。

29
00:01:06,820 --> 00:01:07,820
Allergic.
过敏。

30
00:01:07,820 --> 00:01:08,820
Allergic.
过敏。

31
00:01:08,820 --> 00:01:09,820
Allergic.
过敏。

32
00:01:09,820 --> 00:01:13,780
So when you're allergic to something...
所以当你对某样东西过敏时……

33
00:01:13,780 --> 00:01:14,860
It makes you sick.
它会让你生病。

34
00:01:14,860 --> 00:01:16,940
That one thing makes you sick.
那样东西让你生病。

35
00:01:16,940 --> 00:01:20,260
For example, I'm allergic to seafood.
比如，我对海鲜过敏。

36
00:01:20,260 --> 00:01:23,380
If I eat seafood, I cannot breathe.
如果我吃了海鲜，我就无法呼吸。

37
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,780
Oh, okay, so you definitely want to stay away from fish.
哦，好的，那你肯定要远离鱼了。

38
00:01:26,780 --> 00:01:27,980
Yes, yes.
是的，是的。

39
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:30,540
Some people are allergic to nuts, like peanuts.
有些人对坚果过敏，比如花生。

40
00:01:30,540 --> 00:01:31,540
Or maybe milk.
或者牛奶。

41
00:01:31,540 --> 00:01:32,540
Milk.
牛奶。

42
00:01:32,540 --> 00:01:33,540
Yeah.
嗯。

43
00:01:33,540 --> 00:01:34,540
Cool.
酷。

44
00:01:34,540 --> 00:01:37,900
So when one type of food makes you sick, you are allergic to that food.
所以，当一种食物让你生病时，你就对这种食物过敏。

45
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,380
Okay, great.
好的，很好。

46
00:01:39,380 --> 00:01:44,180
So with this in mind, now we can listen to our dialogue for the first time at its normal
那么，记住这一点，现在我们第一次以正常速度听对话。

47
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:45,180
speed.
速度。

48
00:01:45,180 --> 00:01:47,460
But don't worry if you don't get everything now because...
但如果你现在没完全听懂也别担心，因为……

49
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:55,500
We'll come back and teach you the important language.
我们会回来教你重要的语言点。

50
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:57,620
Do you two have any plans for the evening?
你们俩今晚有什么计划吗？

51
00:01:57,620 --> 00:02:00,620
We were thinking of checking out a restaurant in the neighborhood.
我们正考虑去附近的一家餐馆看看。

52
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,620
Do you have any suggestions?
你有什么建议吗？

53
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:04,340
I know this really nice Italian place.
我知道一家很不错的意大利餐厅。

54
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:07,540
The food is fantastic and the decor is beautiful.
食物很棒，装修也很漂亮。

55
00:02:07,540 --> 00:02:09,940
I'd recommend giving it a try.
我推荐你去试试。

56
00:02:09,940 --> 00:02:12,920
Actually, I'm not all that crazy about Italian food.
其实，我对意大利菜没那么热衷。

57
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,940
I'm in the mood for something a bit lighter.
我想吃点清淡的。

58
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:17,460
In that case, I know a great little bistro.
那样的话，我知道一家很棒的小酒馆。

59
00:02:17,460 --> 00:02:20,100
They make a really tasty seafood platter.
他们做的海鲜拼盘非常好吃。

60
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:22,060
The fish is outstanding.
鱼做得特别出色。

61
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:26,220
It sounds fantastic, but I'm allergic to seafood, so...
听起来很棒，但我对海鲜过敏，所以……

62
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:29,060
Okay, well, let me think.
好吧，让我想想。

63
00:02:29,060 --> 00:02:31,940
Oh, I know this great little place.
哦，我知道一家很棒的小店。

64
00:02:31,940 --> 00:02:35,780
It's just a hole in the wall, but they do the most amazing sandwiches.
那家店虽然不起眼，但他们做的三明治超级好吃。

65
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:37,780
You could give them a try.
你可以去试试。

66
00:02:37,780 --> 00:02:48,260
Ella, you took me there last time I visited and I got food poisoning, remember?
艾拉，上次我来的时候你带我去过那里，结果我食物中毒了，还记得吗？

67
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:52,020
Well I'm getting hungry just thinking about all of those great restaurants.
光是想想那些好餐厅我就饿了。

68
00:02:52,020 --> 00:02:55,980
Yeah, some really good recommendations except for food poisoning, right?
是啊，推荐得都不错，除了食物中毒那次，对吧？

69
00:02:55,980 --> 00:02:57,780
No, not so good.
不，那次不太好。

70
00:02:57,780 --> 00:03:02,840
Let's start with our language takeaway for this lesson.
让我们开始这节课的语言要点吧。

71
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,300
Language takeaway.
语言要点。

72
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:09,380
Our first word on language takeaway is check out.
语言要点的第一个词是 check out。

73
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:10,540
Check out.
Check out。

74
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:11,540
Check out.
Check out。

75
00:03:11,540 --> 00:03:12,740
Check out.
Check out。

76
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:17,100
So we have some great examples on how we can use check out in different situations and
所以我们有一些很好的例子，展示如何在不同情况下使用 check out，

77
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:19,820
then you can understand the meaning.
然后你就能理解它的意思了。

78
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:20,820
Example one.
例子一。

79
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:24,220
Have you been to the new cafe next door?
你去过隔壁那家新开的咖啡馆吗？

80
00:03:24,220 --> 00:03:25,940
Yeah, I checked it out yesterday.
去过，我昨天去看了看。

81
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:30,760
The food was great.
食物很棒。

82
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:32,380
Example two.
例子二。

83
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:40,380
Hey, check out my new car.
嘿，看看我的新车。

84
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:44,380
Example three.
例子三。

85
00:03:44,380 --> 00:03:49,940
I'm going to check out that new shopping mall this weekend.
我这周末要去看看那个新开的购物中心。

86
00:03:49,940 --> 00:03:52,340
So I can understand that it just means look at.
所以我能理解它只是表示“看”的意思。

87
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:54,620
Yeah, look at or yeah or go see.
对，就是“看”或者“去看看”。

88
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:57,020
So let's go check out that new bar in town.
那我们去看看镇上那家新开的酒吧吧。

89
00:03:57,020 --> 00:03:58,540
Yeah, okay, cool.
好，没问题。

90
00:03:58,540 --> 00:04:00,340
Next word is bistro.
下一个词是bistro。

91
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:01,340
Bistro.
Bistro。

92
00:04:01,340 --> 00:04:02,340
Bistro.
Bistro。

93
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:03,340
Bistro.
Bistro。

94
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:05,700
So what's a bistro?
那么什么是bistro？

95
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:11,300
It's kind of complicated, but it's like a small restaurant that's not really cheap though.
有点复杂，但就像一家小餐馆，不过不是很便宜。

96
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:14,140
Not so cheap, but not so expensive.
不算便宜，但也不算贵。

97
00:04:14,140 --> 00:04:15,980
And it's usually French.
而且通常是法式的。

98
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:16,980
Yes.
是的。

99
00:04:16,980 --> 00:04:19,260
So yeah, small informal restaurant.
所以，就是小型非正式餐馆。

100
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:20,820
Yeah, bistro.
对，bistro。

101
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:26,740
Okay, so our third phrase for today is not all that crazy about.
好的，那我们今天的第三个短语是not all that crazy about。

102
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:28,780
Not all that crazy about.
Not all that crazy about。

103
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:31,740
I'm not all that crazy about.
I'm not all that crazy about。

104
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:37,620
Okay, again, kind of a funny phrase, but we've got some examples that will help you understand
好的，这个短语有点有趣，但我们有一些例子可以帮助你理解

105
00:04:37,620 --> 00:04:40,180
the meaning.
它的意思。

106
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:41,180
Example one.
例子一。

107
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:46,580
Do you want to go shopping with me tomorrow?
你明天想和我一起去购物吗？

108
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:48,780
I'm not all that crazy about shopping.
我不太喜欢购物。

109
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:54,580
I don't like spending money.
我不喜欢花钱。

110
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:55,580
Example two.
例子二。

111
00:04:55,580 --> 00:04:58,580
I'm not crazy about jazz music.
我不太喜欢爵士乐。

112
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:05,220
Can I change the song?
我能换首歌吗？

113
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:09,100
So this is just a really polite way of saying you don't like something.
所以这是一种非常礼貌的表达不喜欢的方式。

114
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,100
Exactly.
没错。

115
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:12,860
But now the opposite of this would be tasty.
但它的反义词是tasty。

116
00:05:12,860 --> 00:05:13,860
Tasty.
Tasty。

117
00:05:13,860 --> 00:05:16,460
That's our fourth word, tasty.
这是我们的第四个词，tasty。

118
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:17,580
Tasty.
Tasty。

119
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:20,020
So when something is tasty, it's good.
所以当某样东西tasty，就是好吃。

120
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:21,020
It's good.
好吃。

121
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,020
Like delicious.
比如美味。

122
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:23,020
Delicious.
美味。

123
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,020
Yeah.
是的。

124
00:05:24,020 --> 00:05:25,020
You know what?
你知道吗？

125
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:28,540
In English, we almost never say the food is delicious, but we always say it's really
在英语中，我们几乎不说食物很美味，而是常说它很

126
00:05:28,540 --> 00:05:29,540
tasty.
好吃。

127
00:05:29,540 --> 00:05:30,540
Yes.
对。

128
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:31,540
This is really tasty.
这个真好吃。

129
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:32,540
Yes.
对。

130
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:33,540
Okay.
好的。

131
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:34,540
Tasty.
好吃。

132
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:38,060
And our last phrase for language takeaway, in the mood for.
我们语言摘录的最后一个短语是“有心情做某事”。

133
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:39,860
In the mood for.
有心情做某事。

134
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:41,860
In the mood for.
有心情做某事。

135
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:45,800
Let's listen to some examples of this phrase and we'll understand the meaning a little
我们来听一些这个短语的例子，这样就能更好地理解它的意思。

136
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,700
bit better.
更好一点。

137
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:50,680
Example one.
例子一。

138
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,700
We always eat hamburgers for dinner.
我们晚餐总是吃汉堡。

139
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:57,780
I'm in the mood for something different.
我想吃点不一样的。

140
00:05:57,780 --> 00:06:01,300
Example two.
例子二。

141
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:02,540
Let's watch a movie.
我们看电影吧。

142
00:06:02,540 --> 00:06:04,660
How about Texas Chainsaw Massacre?
《德州电锯杀人狂》怎么样？

143
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:10,000
I am not in the mood for a horror movie.
我没心情看恐怖片。

144
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:17,020
So if I'm in the mood for something, I feel like doing or eating or watching.
所以如果我说“有心情做某事”，就是我想做、想吃或想看什么。

145
00:06:17,020 --> 00:06:18,940
It means you want to do that now.
意思是你现在就想做那件事。

146
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:19,940
Yeah.
对。

147
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:21,500
I'm in the mood for.
我有心情做某事。

148
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:22,500
Okay.
好的。

149
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,660
Some great language we just looked at.
我们刚刚学了一些很棒的语言点。

150
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:34,340
And I think it's time for us to listen to the dialogue a second time.
我想是时候再听一遍对话了。

151
00:06:34,340 --> 00:06:38,020
Do you two have any plans for the evening?
你们俩今晚有什么计划吗？

152
00:06:38,020 --> 00:06:41,880
We were thinking of checking out a restaurant in the neighbourhood.
我们正考虑去附近的一家餐馆看看。

153
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:44,540
Do you have any suggestions?
你有什么建议吗？

154
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:47,860
I know this really nice Italian place.
我知道一家很不错的意大利餐厅。

155
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:52,660
The food is fantastic and the decor is beautiful.
食物很棒，装修也很漂亮。

156
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:55,380
I'd recommend giving it a try.
我推荐去试试。

157
00:06:55,380 --> 00:07:00,220
Actually, I'm not all that crazy about Italian food.
其实，我对意大利菜不太感兴趣。

158
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:04,180
I'm in the mood for something a bit lighter.
我想吃点清淡的。

159
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:07,400
In that case, I know a great little bistro.
那样的话，我知道一家很棒的小酒馆。

160
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:10,440
They make a really tasty seafood platter.
他们做的海鲜拼盘非常好吃。

161
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:13,480
The fish is outstanding.
这鱼非常好吃。

162
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:16,100
It sounds fantastic.
听起来很棒。

163
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:19,140
But I'm allergic to seafood, so...
但是我对海鲜过敏，所以……

164
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:20,140
Okay.
好吧。

165
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:22,140
Well, let me think.
嗯，让我想想。

166
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:25,620
Oh, I know this great little place.
哦，我知道一家很棒的小店。

167
00:07:25,620 --> 00:07:31,580
It's just a hole in the wall, but they do the most amazing sandwiches.
那家店虽然不起眼，但他们做的三明治超级好吃。

168
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:34,300
You've got to give them a try.
你一定要去试试。

169
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:43,060
Ella, you took me there last time I visited and I got food poisoning, remember?
艾拉，上次我来的时候你带我去过那家店，结果我食物中毒了，还记得吗？

170
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:47,440
Okay, some really great and useful phrases there.
好的，这里有一些非常棒且实用的短语。

171
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:50,340
And I know you want to talk about specifically some of these phrases.
我知道你想专门谈谈其中的一些短语。

172
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:51,340
Yes.
是的。

173
00:07:51,340 --> 00:07:55,180
So, today's lesson is all about making recommendations, right?
那么，今天的课程全是关于如何提出建议，对吧？

174
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:56,180
Right.
对。

175
00:07:56,180 --> 00:08:00,820
So, let's look at some useful phrases in Fluency Builder.
我们来看看“流利度构建器”中的一些实用短语。

176
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:01,820
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

177
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:05,700
So, in the dialogue, we heard a great way of asking for a suggestion.
在对话中，我们听到了一种很好的寻求建议的方式。

178
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:06,700
That's right.
没错。

179
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:07,700
Let's listen.
我们来听一下。

180
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:11,180
Do you have any suggestions?
你有什么建议吗？

181
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:13,060
Do you have any suggestions?
你有什么建议吗？

182
